description.narrative: Education stakeholders have increased capacities to identify and respond to learning needs of children not attending school and/or are at risk of dropping out, particularly in target countries.,which contributes to Equitable Access To Quality Education, Learning Outcomes. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, more pre-primary, primary and lower secondary school aged and school-aged children particularly the most vulnerable, are in school and learning.

description.narrative: Pacific countries have strengthened partnerships, strategies and programmes for evidence-based education sector plans. FSM, Marshall Islands, Kiribati and Vanuatu are developing education sector plans with funding from GPE, Solomon Islands will initiate the same in 2020, and Vanuatu is working to strengthen evidence-based school planning linked to the national sector plan. The Pacific region has expanded partnerships and frameworks for inclusive education, Vanuatu has strengthened data on children with disabilities through EMIS, and Solomon Islands has finalized a teacher manual and pilot plan for in-service training on inclusive education. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
